Benefits:
• Map Organizers may bid on tournaments hosted by the Alchemy Alliance. If the map pack designed by the organizer is selected, then they will have the satisfaction of seeing that vision played in a competitive scene. If their map pack is not selected, it will still be played in community games, while continuing to be improved and perhaps eventually winning a tournament.

Requirements:
• Be an Alchemy Affiliate.
• Prepare Component and General Specifications stipulating what the various random maps in the pack need to be, leaving flexibility and freedom for the map makers to feel invested.
• Inspect random maps supplied by scripters against the requirements of their specifications. Disposition any non-conformities.
• For non-conforming maps with inflexible requirements, offer solutions (where possible) for how to achieve map objectives.
• For non-conforming maps with design flexibility, revise requirements to accommodate limitations of map creator or AOE2 scripting engine.
• Assign Consultants to provide feedback and perform competitivity analysis on random maps.  

Additional Notes:
• This is both a passive and active role. It may be awarded because someone is already organizing map packs out of their own interest, or because the map pack is intended for use in an Alchemy Alliance-affiliated tournament. The role may involve "responsibilities" of ensuring that the map pack meets the needs of the tournament.
